Korea Resources, Capstone Buy Far West Mining for $700 Million

-- B y   E u n k y u n g   S e o
-- 
2011-04-17T17:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/korea-resources-capstone-buy-far-west-mining-for-700-million.html
Korea Resources Corp. and Capstone
Mining Corp. have acquired Far West Mining Ltd. for $700 million,
the South Korean company said.  Korea Resources and  Canada ’s Capstone signed a contract on
April 16 to purchase Vancouver-based Far West, a minerals
explorer. Korea Resources put up $400 million, the Seoul-based
company said in a statement.  The terms of the acquisition give Korea Resources the
right to sell half the copper produced at Far West’s Santo
Domingo mine, according to the statement.  Korea Resources also said that it plans to establish an
offshore unit to oversee its copper businesses in Central and
South America and list shares in Canada.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eunkyung Seo in Seoul at 
